## Backend Tool-Registry Implementation Report

I've thoroughly explored the backend tool-registry implementation at `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain-v1/lahore-v1/`. Here's a complete overview of the existing API endpoints, data models, and implementation details.

---

### 1. REST API Endpoints

**Credential Provider Management:**
- **POST /api/workspaces/:workspaceId/providers** — Create a credential provider
  - Request: `{ name, display_name, auth_method, authorization_url?, token_url?, client_id?, client_secret?, scopes?, api_key_header? }`
  - Response: `{ id, name, display_name, auth_method, has_client_secret, authorization_url?, token_url?, client_id?, scopes?, api_key_header?, created_at }`
  - Status: 201 Created | 400 Bad Request | 409 Conflict (duplicate name)

- **GET /api/workspaces/:workspaceId/providers** — List all credential providers in workspace
  - Response: `{ providers: ProviderApiResponse[] }`
  - Status: 200 OK

**Connected Account Management:**
- **POST /api/workspaces/:workspaceId/accounts/connect/:providerId** — Initiate account connection
  - For OAuth2: Returns `{ redirect_url, state }` for redirect flow
  - For API key/bearer/basic: Request body with credentials, returns `{ id, provider_id, status, has_api_key, has_bearer_token, has_basic_credentials, has_access_token, connected_at }`
  - Status: 200 OK (OAuth2 redirect) | 201 Created (static credentials) | 409 Conflict (account already exists)

- **GET /api/workspaces/:workspaceId/accounts** — List connected accounts for authenticated identity
  - Response: `{ accounts: ConnectedAccountApiResponse[] }`
  - Status: 200 OK

- **DELETE /api/workspaces/:workspaceId/accounts/:accountId** — Revoke a connected account
  - Response: `{ status: "revoked" }`
  - Hard-deletes all encrypted credential fields; idempotent
  - Status: 200 OK | 404 Not Found

**OAuth2 Callback:**
- **GET /api/workspaces/:workspaceId/accounts/oauth2/callback** — OAuth2 redirect URI (referenced in code but not explicitly routed in provided excerpt)
  - Exchanges authorization code for tokens
  - Stores tokens in connected_account with encryption

---

### 2. SurrealDB Schema

**Table: `mcp_tool` (SCHEMAFULL)**
```surql
DEFINE TABLE mcp_tool SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD name ON mcp_tool TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD toolkit ON mcp_tool TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD description ON mcp_tool TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD input_schema ON mcp_tool TYPE object FLEXIBLE;
DEFINE FIELD output_schema ON mcp_tool TYPE option<object> FLEXIBLE;
DEFINE FIELD provider ON mcp_tool TYPE option<record<credential_provider>>;
DEFINE FIELD risk_level ON mcp_tool TYPE string ASSERT $value IN ["low", "medium", "high", "critical"];
DEFINE FIELD workspace ON mcp_tool TYPE record<workspace>;
DEFINE FIELD status ON mcp_tool TYPE string ASSERT $value IN ["active", "disabled"];
DEFINE FIELD created_at ON mcp_tool TYPE datetime DEFAULT time::now();
-- Indexes
DEFINE INDEX mcp_tool_workspace ON mcp_tool FIELDS workspace;
DEFINE INDEX mcp_tool_workspace_name ON mcp_tool FIELDS workspace, name;
DEFINE INDEX mcp_tool_workspace_toolkit ON mcp_tool FIELDS workspace, toolkit;
DEFINE INDEX mcp_tool_workspace_status ON mcp_tool FIELDS workspace, status;
```

**Table: `credential_provider` (SCHEMAFULL)**
```surql
DEFINE TABLE credential_provider SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD name ON credential_provider TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD display_name ON credential_provider TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD auth_method ON credential_provider TYPE string ASSERT $value IN ["oauth2", "api_key", "bearer", "basic"];
DEFINE FIELD workspace ON credential_provider TYPE record<workspace>;
DEFINE FIELD authorization_url ON credential_provider TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD token_url ON credential_provider TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD client_id ON credential_provider TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD client_secret_encrypted ON credential_provider TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD scopes ON credential_provider TYPE option<array<string>>;
DEFINE FIELD api_key_header ON credential_provider TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD created_at ON credential_provider TYPE datetime DEFAULT time::now();
-- Indexes
DEFINE INDEX credential_provider_workspace ON credential_provider FIELDS workspace;
DEFINE INDEX credential_provider_workspace_name ON credential_provider FIELDS workspace, name;
```

**Table: `connected_account` (SCHEMAFULL)**
```surql
DEFINE TABLE connected_account SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD identity ON connected_account TYPE record<identity>;
DEFINE FIELD provider ON connected_account TYPE record<credential_provider>;
DEFINE FIELD workspace ON connected_account TYPE record<workspace>;
DEFINE FIELD status ON connected_account TYPE string ASSERT $value IN ["active", "revoked", "expired"];
DEFINE FIELD access_token_encrypted ON connected_account TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD refresh_token_encrypted ON connected_account TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD token_expires_at ON connected_account TYPE option<datetime>;
DEFINE FIELD api_key_encrypted ON connected_account TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD basic_username ON connected_account TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD basic_password_encrypted ON connected_account TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD bearer_token_encrypted ON connected_account TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD scopes ON connected_account TYPE option<array<string>>;
DEFINE FIELD connected_at ON connected_account TYPE datetime DEFAULT time::now();
DEFINE FIELD updated_at ON connected_account TYPE datetime DEFAULT time::now();
-- Indexes
DEFINE INDEX connected_account_identity_provider ON connected_account FIELDS identity, provider;
DEFINE INDEX connected_account_workspace ON connected_account FIELDS workspace;
DEFINE INDEX connected_account_identity ON connected_account FIELDS identity;
```

**Relation Table: `can_use` (TYPE RELATION IN identity OUT mcp_tool)**
```surql
DEFINE TABLE can_use TYPE RELATION IN identity OUT mcp_tool SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD granted_at ON can_use TYPE datetime DEFAULT time::now();
DEFINE FIELD max_calls_per_hour ON can_use TYPE option<int>;
DEFINE INDEX can_use_identity ON can_use FIELDS in;
DEFINE INDEX can_use_tool ON can_use FIELDS out;
```

**Relation Table: `governs_tool` (TYPE RELATION IN policy OUT mcp_tool)**
```surql
DEFINE TABLE governs_tool TYPE RELATION IN policy OUT mcp_tool SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD conditions ON governs_tool TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD max_per_call ON governs_tool TYPE option<int>;
DEFINE FIELD max_per_day ON governs_tool TYPE option<int>;
DEFINE INDEX governs_tool_policy ON governs_tool FIELDS in;
DEFINE INDEX governs_tool_tool ON governs_tool FIELDS out;
```

---

### 3. Encryption Implementation

**File:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain-v1/lahore-v1/app/src/server/tool-registry/encryption.ts`

**Algorithm:** AES-256-GCM
- **IV Length:** 12 bytes (random per encryption)
- **Auth Tag Length:** 16 bytes
- **Key:** 256-bit (32-byte) hex string from `TOOL_ENCRYPTION_KEY` env var
- **Format:** base64(IV || ciphertext || authTag)

**Functions:**
- `encryptSecret(plaintext: string, keyHex: string): string` — Encrypts plaintext, returns base64 ciphertext
- `decryptSecret(ciphertextBase64: string, keyHex: string): string` — Decrypts base64 ciphertext

**Encrypted Fields:**
- `credential_provider.client_secret_encrypted`
- `connected_account.access_token_encrypted`
- `connected_account.refresh_token_encrypted`
- `connected_account.api_key_encrypted`
- `connected_account.basic_password_encrypted`
- `connected_account.bearer_token_encrypted`

---

### 4. OAuth2 Flow Implementation

**File:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain-v1/lahore-v1/app/src/server/tool-registry/oauth-flow.ts`

**State Management:**
- In-memory Map keyed by state parameter (sufficient for walking skeleton; production should use DB records)
- TTL: 10 minutes per state entry
- State format: UUID (generated via `crypto.randomUUID()`)

**Key Functions:**
- `buildAuthorizationUrl(provider, redirectUri, state): string` — Constructs OAuth2 authorization URL with client_id, redirect_uri, scopes, state, response_type=code
- `exchangeCodeForTokens(provider, code, redirectUri, clientSecret): Promise<TokenExchangeResult>` — Exchanges authorization code for tokens via POST to token_url
- `storeOAuthState(state, entry): void` — Stores state with context (providerId, identityId, workspaceId, createdAt)
- `consumeOAuthState(state): OAuthStateEntry | undefined` — Retrieves and deletes state entry, returns undefined if expired

**Token Exchange Response:**
```typescript
{
  access_token: string;
  refresh_token?: string;
  expires_in?: number;
  scope?: string;
}
```

---

### 5. Credential Resolution Pipeline

**File:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain-v1/lahore-v1/app/src/server/proxy/credential-resolver.ts`

**Resolution Chain:**
1. Look up `mcp_tool` by name → get provider reference
2. Load `credential_provider` record → get auth_method + config
3. Find `connected_account` for identity + provider (status=active)
4. Decrypt credential fields
5. Build auth headers based on auth_method

**Auth Header Building:**
- **oauth2:** `Authorization: Bearer {access_token}`
- **api_key:** `{apiKeyHeader}: {decrypted_api_key}` (default header: `X-API-Key`)
- **bearer:** `Authorization: Bearer {decrypted_bearer_token}`
- **basic:** `Authorization: Basic {base64(username:password)}`

**Token Refresh (OAuth2):**
- Detects expired tokens via `token_expires_at`
- Calls provider's token_url with grant_type=refresh_token
- Updates encrypted tokens in connected_account
- Marks account as "expired" if refresh fails

**Error Handling:**
- Missing account → "Provider account not connected"
- Revoked account → "Provider account disconnected"
- Expired credentials → "Provider credentials expired, please reconnect"
- Decrypt failures → error propagated to LLM

---

### 6. Query Layer

**File:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain-v1/lahore-v1/app/src/server/tool-registry/queries.ts`

**Key Queries:**
- `providerNameExists(surreal, workspaceRecord, name): Promise<boolean>`
- `createProvider(surreal, workspaceRecord, content): Promise<CredentialProviderRecord>`
- `listProviders(surreal, workspaceRecord): Promise<CredentialProviderRecord[]>`
- `getProviderById(surreal, providerId): Promise<CredentialProviderRecord | undefined>`
- `activeAccountExists(surreal, identityRecord, providerRecord): Promise<boolean>`
- `createConnectedAccount(surreal, content): Promise<ConnectedAccountRecord>`
- `listConnectedAccounts(surreal, identityRecord, workspaceRecord): Promise<ConnectedAccountRecord[]>`
- `revokeConnectedAccount(surreal, accountRecord, identityRecord, workspaceRecord): Promise<ConnectedAccountRecord | undefined>`
  - Sets status to "revoked"
  - Hard-deletes all encrypted credential fields (sets to NONE)
  - Idempotent

**Governance Queries:**
- `fetchGovernancePolicies(surreal, toolName): Promise<GovernsPolicyRow[]>` — Fetches active governs_tool edges with policy metadata
- `countTodayToolExecutions(surreal, toolName, workspaceId): Promise<number>` — Counts successful tool calls since UTC midnight
- `countHourlyToolExecutions(surreal, toolName, workspaceId, identityId): Promise<number>` — Counts successful tool calls in last hour for identity
- `fetchCanUseRateLimit(surreal, identityId, toolName): Promise<{ maxCallsPerHour?: number }>` — Fetches per-identity rate limit

---

### 7. Authorization & Permissions

**DPoP-Based Auth:**
- All endpoints require DPoP token with `urn:brain:workspace` claim
- Identity extracted from request header `X-Brain-Identity` (set by DPoP middleware)
- Workspace resolved from DPoP token claim (not URL parameter)
- `member_of` edge required between identity and workspace

**Scope Restrictions:**
- **Provider creation:** Workspace admin (implicit via workspace scope)
- **Account connection:** Authenticated identity can connect for itself only
- **Account listing:** Identity sees only their own connected accounts
- **Account revocation:** Identity can only revoke their own accounts

---

### 8. Request/Response Type Definitions

**CreateProviderInput:**
```typescript
{
  name: string;
  display_name: string;
  auth_method: "oauth2" | "api_key" | "bearer" | "basic";
  authorization_url?: string;
  token_url?: string;
  client_id?: string;
  client_secret?: string;  // Plaintext in request, encrypted before storage
  scopes?: string[];
  api_key_header?: string;
}
```

**ProviderApiResponse:**
```typescript
{
  id: string;
  name: string;
  display_name: string;
  auth_method: string;
  has_client_secret: boolean;  // Boolean flag, never returns plaintext
  authorization_url?: string;
  token_url?: string;
  client_id?: string;
  scopes?: string[];
  api_key_header?: string;
  created_at: string;  // ISO 8601
}
```

**ConnectAccountInput:**
```typescript
{
  api_key?: string;
  bearer_token?: string;
  basic_username?: string;
  basic_password?: string;
}
```

**ConnectedAccountApiResponse:**
```typescript
{
  id: string;
  provider_id: string;
  status: "active" | "revoked" | "expired";
  has_api_key: boolean;
  has_bearer_token: boolean;
  has_basic_credentials: boolean;
  has_access_token: boolean;  // OAuth2 only
  connected_at: string;  // ISO 8601
}
```

---

### 9. Implementation Files

| File Path | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `app/src/server/tool-registry/routes.ts` | HTTP request handlers (provider/account CRUD) |
| `app/src/server/tool-registry/types.ts` | Domain type definitions |
| `app/src/server/tool-registry/encryption.ts` | AES-256-GCM encryption/decryption |
| `app/src/server/tool-registry/oauth-flow.ts` | OAuth2 authorization URL builder, token exchange, state management |
| `app/src/server/tool-registry/queries.ts` | SurrealDB queries (CRUD + governance) |
| `app/src/server/proxy/credential-resolver.ts` | Credential resolution & token refresh pipeline |
| `app/src/server/proxy/tool-executor.ts` | Tool execution with governance enforcement |
| `schema/surreal-schema.surql` | Database schema (mcp_tool, credential_provider, connected_account, can_use, governs_tool tables) |
| `tests/acceptance/tool-registry/tool-registry-test-kit.ts` | Test helpers & seed functions |

---

### 10. Configuration

**Environment Variables:**
- `TOOL_ENCRYPTION_KEY` — 256-bit hex string for AES-256-GCM (required for credential encryption)

**Route Registration:**
- Routes registered in `app/src/server/runtime/start-server.ts` (lines 404-444)

This comprehensive implementation provides a complete credential management system for integrating external tools via OAuth2 and static authentication methods, with strong encryption, governance policies, and rate limiting support.

