# Frontend Codebase Architecture Patterns - Brain UI

## 1. ROUTER SETUP (TanStack Router)

**File:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain-v1/lahore-v1/app/src/client/router.tsx`

**Pattern:**
- TanStack Router v1 with route tree architecture
- Route definitions use `createRoute()` with parent route chaining via `getParentRoute()`
- Root route splits into public (`/sign-in`, `/consent`) and authenticated layout (`/`)
- Authenticated routes share `AppShell` layout with sidebar, header, and main content area
- Routes support search params via `validateSearch()` functions

**Key Routes:**
```
/ (home)
/chat, /chat/$conversationId
/graph
/review/$sessionId
/learnings
/policies, /policies/$policyId
```

**Auth Pattern:**
- `beforeLoad` hook checks session via `authClient.getSession()`
- Redirects to `/sign-in` if not authenticated
- Search params support redirect target preservation

---

## 2. SIDEBAR NAVIGATION

**File:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain-v1/lahore-v1/app/src/client/components/layout/WorkspaceSidebar.tsx`

**Structure:**
- Fixed width (200px), scrollable, border-right layout
